n = arr.shape[1]
    # The FFT can be performed using scipy.fftpack.fft, but it doesn't have an option to zero-pad.
    # Using numpy.fft.fft, we can zero-pad, but it doesn't use the FFTW library, which is faster.
    # So, we will combine these two methods to achieve both zero-padding and FFTW acceleration.
    coeffs = np.array([np.fft.fft(row, n=n) for row in arr])
    coeffs = fftpack.fft(coeffs, n=n)

    fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1)
    ax.plot(abs(coeffs), label='Absolute values of FFT coefficients')
    ax.set_title('Absolute values of FFT coefficients')
    ax.set_xlabel('Index')
    ax.set_ylabel('Absolute Value')
    ax.legend()
    plt.show()

    return ax
